# Core Engineering

- New code must preserve the current supported runtime shape unless the task explicitly changes it: FastAPI API, Vue frontend, MySQL persistence, per-tenant worker, scheduler-in-worker, local output files, and current integrations.
- New backend code must reuse existing core concepts and status models such as `Task`, `Job`, `Tenant`, `ScheduleRule`, and `ScheduleLog` instead of introducing parallel workflow concepts.
- When modifying existing code, move repeated workflow logic toward shared backend services instead of copying it into another route, script, or integration module.
- Do not introduce additional dead code paths, legacy compatibility fields, or duplicate service variants.
- When a change updates runtime behavior, config behavior, or architecture direction, update the relevant docs in the same task.
